In general virtualization of course costs something and probably your assumption is correct, however personally I see some things that can be fixed here. Having them fixed let&#39;s redo the experiment and compare the numbers again.

First of all, benchmark is not a test - you should rather return `boolean` value from your benchmark method instead of doing assertion. Assuming we already know the calculation is correct I&#39;d rewrite the code as:
```java
@Benchmark
@Threads(16)
@Fork(jvmArgsAppend = {&quot;-XX:+UseZGC&quot;})
public boolean ECDSA() {
  return ecdsaSign.secp256Verify(hash, ecKeyPair.getPublicKey(), signatureData);
}
```
Second, you run the benchmar in 16 threads, but from the screenshots I see that on Windows you have 15 workers and only 12 on Ubuntu. Please double check whether you have the same number of threads everywhere.

Third, it looks like you are running your benchmark from IDEA. In general this approach is not wrong, however it&#39;s more correct to run the benchmark from command line, e.g. `user@mymachine:~/IdeaProjects/your-jmh-project$java -jar target/benchmarks.jar ...`. In this particular case IDEA is a Java application run on the same machine as the benchmark, so when you specify 16 threads (same as number of cores of the CPU) you must understand, that in practise some of JMH workers could be competing with other threads for CPU cores and other workers could monopolize their cores. In addition you have OS utilizing the same cores and the number of OS threads is likely to be different for Windows and Linux. Let&#39;s  try to reduce the number of JMH threads, e.g. by using `@Threads(4)`. 

Fourth, as of your output it looks like forked VMs peek up options from command line: `# VM options: -XX:ThreadPriorityPolicy=1 -XX:+UnlockExperimentalVMOptions -XX:+EnableJVMCIProduct -XX:-UnlockExperimentalVMOptions -Dvisualvm.id=26191149540700 -ea -Didea.test.cyclic.buffer.size=1048576 -javaagent:C:\Program Files\JetBrains\IntelliJ IDEA Community Edition 2021.1.1\lib\idea_rt.jar=51600:C:\Program Files\JetBrains\IntelliJ IDEA Community Edition 2021.1.1\bin -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8 -XX:+UseZGC
`
I&#39;d double check whether you actually need them (apart from `-XX:+UseZGC`).

